    "For example, in \"In the second week after hatching eagle chicks can hold up their heads\", \"their\" is an anaphor, referring back to the eagle chicks.)",
    "Artificial neural network: a type of machine learning model comprising a collection of connected units or nodes called artificial neurons organised into layers.",
    "Each connection between neurons has an associated weight.",
    "The process of training a neural network involves feeding it labelled training data, and adjusting the weights and biases during each iteration to minimise the difference between the predicted outputs and the true labels."
